{{no footnotes|date=May 2014}} The '''Institute for Condensed Matter Theory''' ('''ICMT''') is an institute for the research of [[condensed matter physics|condensed matter theory]] hosted by and located at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign]].
ICMT was founded in 2007. The first director of the institute was [[Paul Goldbart]] who was followed by [[Eduardo Fradkin]]. The chief scientist is Nobel laureate [[Anthony Leggett]].
